equals(EObject, EObject) - Method in class lu.uni.geko.util.ecore.ReusableEqualityHelper
A re-implementation of EcoreUtil.EqualityHelper.equals(EObject, EObject)that makes instances ready for reuse for multiple comparisons.

As EqualityHelper only uses methods from the inherited HashMap in the method equals(EObject, EObject) it is sufficient to override this method to make EqualityHelper helper reusable for multiple comparisons.

The developers of EcoreUtil.EqualityHelper assumed (as stated in the JavaDoc) that an EObject is equal to at most one EObject because they assumed that for each new comparison a new Helper will be used.
